19:16.677 --> 19:19.027
Hey, and she might even
have an eye for our colonel.

19:19.158 --> 19:20.898
Yeah, so she's in on
all their schemes.

19:21.029 --> 19:22.683
What do you call this thing?

19:22.813 --> 19:23.901
"Hogan's Heroes."

19:25.642 --> 19:27.035
Have you pitched this
anywhere else?

19:29.211 --> 19:30.778
Don't.

19:30.908 --> 19:32.519
'Cause we're buying it.

19:40.309 --> 19:43.617
"I'll make him
an offer he can't refuse."

19:43.747 --> 19:45.140
Great line.Yeah.

19:45.271 --> 19:47.621
It's fun, isn't it?It's special, Mario.

19:47.751 --> 19:50.145
The Frank Sinatra,
Johnny Fontane character?

19:50.276 --> 19:51.625
Great.

19:51.755 --> 19:55.237
Maybe Sinatra will play him
in the movie, hmm?

19:55.368 --> 19:56.673
Should we call Paramount?

19:56.804 --> 19:59.589
Mario, just because
they optioned it early,

19:59.720 --> 20:01.156
it doesn't mean
it's gonna get made.

20:01.287 --> 20:02.418
Yeah.

20:03.811 --> 20:05.204
Let's make sure
it gets published first.

20:05.334 --> 20:07.597
They say to me,
you can make "Love Story,"

20:07.728 --> 20:08.511
which we agree,

20:09.469 --> 20:09.730
greatest love story
of all time.

20:10.774 --> 20:14.038
But the girl
has to live at the end.

20:14.169 --> 20:15.649
Can you fucking believe that?

20:15.779 --> 20:17.520
Yeah, the death
is what makes it work.

20:17.651 --> 20:20.044
Yes.Look at "Romeo and Juliet."

20:20.175 --> 20:21.742
Not the same story
if they'd lived.

20:21.872 --> 20:23.222
God, no.

20:23.352 --> 20:26.312
We feel the pain of the loss,
feel the grief.

20:26.442 --> 20:29.315
We feel pity.
We--we cry.

20:29.445 --> 20:32.231
I'll make the movie, Bob,
but only if she dies.

20:32.361 --> 20:34.189
You are preaching
to the choir, babe.

20:34.320 --> 20:35.712
Look, you make "Love Story,"

20:35.843 --> 20:38.411
and I will give you
total creative control.

20:38.541 --> 20:40.630
And final cut.And a back end that's real.

20:40.761 --> 20:42.241
We got a chance
to make a huge hit here.

20:42.371 --> 20:45.331
I only make two decisions,
all right?

20:45.461 --> 20:47.463
Hiring you, yes.

20:47.594 --> 20:50.118
Secondly, casting Ali MacGraw.

20:51.598 --> 20:53.077
Bob, I don't know
if I'm comfortable

20:53.208 --> 20:54.601
with hiring your girlfriend.

20:54.731 --> 20:57.212
One of the best actresses
of our time.

20:57.343 --> 21:01.390
Trust me, my friend,
I've seen her up close.

21:01.521 --> 21:03.262
And so should you,
that's all I'm saying.

21:03.392 --> 21:05.699
Sheila, could you send in
our guest, please?

21:05.829 --> 21:06.830
What is this?

21:08.354 --> 21:12.793
Ali MacGraw,
meet Arthur Hiller.

21:12.923 --> 21:15.056
I'm so excited
to be working with you.

21:15.186 --> 21:16.318
Me too.

21:16.449 --> 21:19.147
You two are gonna
make magic together.

21:19.278 --> 21:21.149
I'll let you get acquainted.

21:24.370 --> 21:26.676
I saw your most recent film.

21:26.807 --> 21:28.287
I loved it.Thank you so much.

21:28.417 --> 21:30.985
Sheila,

21:31.115 --> 21:32.508
I'm good.

21:32.639 --> 21:35.903
"In The Still of the Night"]

21:36.033 --> 21:38.862
Lucchese and Gambino
got here about ten minutes ago.

21:45.956 --> 21:48.481
Sinatra's crying to everyone
but the Pope

21:48.611 --> 21:51.353
about this book
that's about to come out:

21:51.484 --> 21:52.920
"The Godfather."

21:53.703 --> 21:55.314
Giving me a fucking headache.

21:55.444 --> 21:56.532
'Cause there's
a character in it

21:56.663 --> 21:59.100
that's supposed to be
a real fighetta,

21:59.230 --> 22:00.406
and everyone thinks it's him.

22:00.536 --> 22:02.190
How'd you know that?

22:02.321 --> 22:03.974
I read it somewhere.

22:08.762 --> 22:10.633
I just have
to use the bathroom.

22:14.420 --> 22:16.335
What have we got here?

22:16.465 --> 22:18.424
He said it was important
to the commission.

22:58.507 --> 23:00.335
Sit down, Joe.
Have a drink.

23:00.466 --> 23:02.381
You're making me nervous
standing like that.

23:05.384 --> 23:06.994
Sit down, Joe.

23:15.045 --> 23:17.570
I've been offered a seat
at the commission table.

23:19.267 --> 23:20.660
My own family.

23:21.661 --> 23:24.403
Well, nobody told me
about that.

23:24.533 --> 23:25.752
Well, it's supposed to be

23:25.882 --> 23:27.580
the last thing
you'll ever hear.

23:32.323 --> 23:33.760
Bonanno.

23:34.674 --> 23:36.240
He came to me a while back,

23:36.371 --> 23:38.678
talking about making changes.

23:38.808 --> 23:40.941
That's what he thinks
I'm doing here right now.

23:42.029 --> 23:44.118
But I'm here to tell you
so you can deal with it

23:44.248 --> 23:45.859
the way the commission chooses.

23:47.774 --> 23:50.516
And then you take
Bonanno's seat at the table?

23:54.128 --> 23:56.565
Well, that's not up to me.
That's up to you.

23:58.262 --> 23:59.829
Hey, I'm an ambitious guy,

23:59.960 --> 24:02.528
but not at the price of
my loyalty to what we do here,

24:02.658 --> 24:04.530
to you and the rest
of the commission.

24:06.445 --> 24:08.185
I respect whatever you decide.

24:09.665 --> 24:11.145
Good night, gentlemen.

24:15.192 --> 24:16.280
Let's go.

24:16.411 --> 24:19.893
Bonanno, he's gotta go.

24:33.559 --> 24:35.256
You maniacs!

24:35.386 --> 24:37.301
You blew it up!

24:37.432 --> 24:39.260
God damn you!

24:40.653 --> 24:44.787
God damn you all to hell!

24:58.105 --> 24:59.933
Uh, are we moving in?

25:01.369 --> 25:02.631
This.

25:03.893 --> 25:05.678
This is what it's all about.

25:07.549 --> 25:08.942
What, monkeys?

25:09.072 --> 25:12.467
No, the excitement,
the thrill.

25:12.598 --> 25:13.686
I mean, did you
hear them at the end?

25:13.816 --> 25:16.689
Yes, uh, that--
that was a great ending.

25:16.819 --> 25:18.560
No, no,
it's not just about the ending,

25:18.691 --> 25:20.780
it's--it's about
the experience of it.

25:20.910 --> 25:23.434
You got 300 people
all watching the same thing,

25:23.565 --> 25:24.827
reacting in real time,

25:24.958 --> 25:26.916
just feeding off each other.

25:29.136 --> 25:31.181
You can't get that experience
in television.

25:32.618 --> 25:33.575
You're just
in your living room,

25:33.706 --> 25:35.229
looking at a small
fucking box.

25:35.359 --> 25:37.361
It's just a different game.

25:37.492 --> 25:38.667
Five years of "Hogan's"
and you can make

25:38.798 --> 25:40.364
all the money you'd ever need.

25:40.495 --> 25:41.540
Five years of "Hogan's,"

25:41.670 --> 25:43.585
I'm gonna shoot myself
in the face.

25:43.716 --> 25:45.544
Hmm.Yeah.

25:45.674 --> 25:46.545
They showed us
the writer's room

25:46.675 --> 25:48.198
at CBS last week.Mm.

25:48.329 --> 25:50.374
It was like an exact
fucking replica of Rand.

25:53.377 --> 25:55.292
It can't just be
about the money.

25:56.250 --> 25:57.991
At first, I thought it was,
this whole Hollywood thing,

25:58.121 --> 26:00.384
but...

26:00.515 --> 26:02.038
my mother,

26:02.169 --> 26:04.040
she was a tough broad,

26:04.171 --> 26:08.001
and she never showed emotion
ever about anything,

26:08.131 --> 26:10.525
except at the movies.

26:10.656 --> 26:12.832
That was the only time
I ever saw my mother cry.

26:16.270 --> 26:19.012
I mean, you can't put a price
on that experience.

26:20.491 --> 26:22.189
I mean, that's magic, baby.

26:25.453 --> 26:27.194
I need to be in the movies.

26:36.333 --> 26:39.946
So what do you know
about producing film?

26:40.076 --> 26:42.209
What do I know
about producing TV?

26:42.339 --> 26:43.297
Good point.

26:44.298 --> 26:45.604
Let's go.

26:47.170 --> 26:48.432
You coming?

26:57.006 --> 26:59.052
Sir.

27:07.756 --> 27:09.410
I'm having a party
Saturday night,

27:09.540 --> 27:10.846
and if you're not there,

27:10.977 --> 27:12.631
well, I'm just gonna send
everybody home,

27:12.761 --> 27:14.458
even Jack and Warren.

27:14.589 --> 27:15.764
Huh?

27:15.895 --> 27:17.679
Nicholson and Beatty.

27:17.810 --> 27:19.681
Ooh, you're gonna love them.

27:19.812 --> 27:22.684
And, uh, bathing suits
are optional.

27:22.815 --> 27:25.121
Barry, what are you doing here?

27:25.252 --> 27:26.862
I hate to interrupt
your little soiree,

27:26.993 --> 27:29.386
but we had a meeting.Oh, relax, Barry.

27:29.517 --> 27:31.562
Have a drink before you have
a heart attack, right, girls?

27:31.693 --> 27:32.912
It's00 in the morning.

27:34.653 --> 27:35.915
Coffee, black.Give us a minute.

27:36.045 --> 27:40.006
I'm sorry.
Every party needs a pooper.

27:49.363 --> 27:52.192
How you doing, Barry?Bob.

27:52.322 --> 27:54.107
Thank you.

27:54.237 --> 27:55.630
I got off the phone
with Charlie.

27:55.761 --> 27:57.023
He's livid.

27:57.153 --> 27:59.329
Paramount has fallen back
to eight out of nine.

27:59.460 --> 28:00.722
Let me guess.

28:00.853 --> 28:02.681
He's up your ass about
"Paint Your Wagon" overages.

28:02.811 --> 28:03.899
Lee Marvin and Clint Eastwood

28:04.030 --> 28:05.509
should be shooting people,
not singing!

28:05.640 --> 28:06.685
That's entertainment.

28:06.815 --> 28:08.077
And what's
with the "Love Story"?

28:08.208 --> 28:10.776
The girl dies at the end?
Who wants to see that?

28:10.906 --> 28:12.038
It's his studio.

28:12.168 --> 28:14.431
Look, I'm not gonna beat
around the bush.

28:14.562 --> 28:16.172
We need hits.

28:16.303 --> 28:18.914
You can't live off of
"Rosemary's Baby" forever.

28:19.828 --> 28:22.178
Barry, did you--
did you read "Love Story"?

28:23.310 --> 28:24.659
Yes.

28:24.790 --> 28:26.530
Why?

28:26.661 --> 28:27.923
Did it move you?

28:28.054 --> 28:30.883
What does that have to do
with anything?

28:31.013 --> 28:32.058
The audience
needs to be moved, Barry.

28:32.188 --> 28:33.973
That's how you make
hit pictures.

28:34.103 --> 28:36.323
Times are changing,
and we need to keep up.

28:36.453 --> 28:38.281
That's why I got the job
in the ivory tower

28:38.412 --> 28:40.240
and you don't.

28:40.370 --> 28:42.590
If you don't string together
some hits,

28:42.721 --> 28:46.725
that ivory tower of yours
is going to come crashing down.

28:51.773 --> 28:54.471
Oh, ye of such little faith.

28:55.603 --> 28:56.778
Bottoms up, Barry.

29:08.442 --> 29:09.791
Bob Evans.
I'm Al Ruddy.

29:09.922 --> 29:11.706
I wanted to talk to you.
You got a minute?

29:11.837 --> 29:13.926
I'm fairly certain
we don't have a meeting,

29:14.056 --> 29:15.971
but you knew that already,
didn't you?

29:16.102 --> 29:17.494
How'd you get on the lot?

29:17.625 --> 29:20.497
Ain't exactly Fort Knox.Fair enough.

29:20.628 --> 29:21.847
What can I do for you,
Mr. Ruddy?

29:21.977 --> 29:23.892
It's what I can do for you.

29:24.023 --> 29:25.720
I wanna produce for Paramount.

29:25.851 --> 29:27.940
You told a good story once.

29:28.070 --> 29:30.464
Ballsy of you to walk away
from "Hogan's Heroes."

29:30.594 --> 29:32.945
So you do know who I am?I know who everyone is, kid.

29:33.075 --> 29:35.295
Look, you know what
a producer does, Mr. Ruddy?

29:35.425 --> 29:37.514
They do whatever it takes
to get their movie made.

29:37.645 --> 29:38.733
Now, what makes you think

29:38.864 --> 29:40.735
that you're qualified
to do that, huh?

29:40.866 --> 29:42.389
You know, I read
an article in "Variety,"

29:42.519 --> 29:44.217
said that you started out
selling ladies' slacks

29:44.347 --> 29:47.133
and doing bit parts in movies,
but you still figured it out.

29:47.263 --> 29:50.179
Don't--don't--
don't call them bit parts

29:50.310 --> 29:51.790
when you're kissing
someone's ass.

29:51.920 --> 29:53.704
I work with Jimmy fucking
Cagney, my friend,

29:53.835 --> 29:55.706
toe-to-toe.

29:55.837 --> 29:59.580
So unknown computer guy

29:59.710 --> 30:02.888
creates CBS's hit comedy
about Nazis.

30:04.193 --> 30:05.716
Go figure.

30:05.847 --> 30:07.936
All right.
All right.

30:08.067 --> 30:10.156
You do remind me of me,
and I'm a sentimental guy,

30:10.286 --> 30:11.810
and you caught me
on a good day.

30:11.940 --> 30:13.855
Let's set a lunch, Mr. Ruddy.

30:15.074 --> 30:16.858
Talk about your future.

30:20.383 --> 30:22.429
What producers
have you worked for?

30:22.559 --> 30:23.996
You'll be my first.

30:24.126 --> 30:25.867
I've worked in legal
for three years

30:25.998 --> 30:28.261
and then saw this job posted.

30:28.391 --> 30:30.872
Well, then, I guess, uh,
we both have a lot to learn.

30:31.003 --> 30:33.179
Thanks.

30:35.964 --> 30:38.749
Thank you.
We'll let you know.

30:38.880 --> 30:40.447
I thought
he just gave me the job.

30:40.577 --> 30:42.449
Oh, no, sweetie.

30:43.102 --> 30:44.799
That was just
his Valium talking.

30:44.930 --> 30:47.236
You are dodging a bullet here.

30:47.367 --> 30:49.282
You can thank me later.
Exit's that way.

30:50.849 --> 30:52.763
Thank you.

30:52.894 --> 30:54.113
All right, bye.

30:57.899 --> 30:59.205
You're Albert Ruddy.

30:59.901 --> 31:00.859
Who are you?

31:00.989 --> 31:02.643
Bettye McCartt.

31:03.600 --> 31:05.124
Bernie Fein sent me.

31:07.866 --> 31:09.519
Bernie.

31:09.650 --> 31:10.825
It's nice to meet you, Bettye,
but I'm sorry.

31:10.956 --> 31:12.653
I just hired somebody.

31:12.783 --> 31:13.959
That little mouse?Yeah.

31:14.089 --> 31:15.351
No.Yeah.

31:15.482 --> 31:17.223
No.

31:21.009 --> 31:22.532
Let me take you on a tour.

31:23.882 --> 31:25.013
Come on.

31:25.709 --> 31:27.102
I don't bite.

31:29.104 --> 31:33.195
That spot
is hallowed fucking ground.

31:33.326 --> 31:34.893
You're not even
paying attention to it.

31:35.023 --> 31:36.851
Look.

31:36.982 --> 31:38.200
The guard gate?

31:40.246 --> 31:42.596
That is where Gloria Swanson

31:42.726 --> 31:46.252
drove onto the lot
in "Sunset Boulevard."

31:47.427 --> 31:48.950
Because she thought
Cecil B. DeMille

31:49.081 --> 31:50.909
wanted to make
her version of "Salome."

31:51.039 --> 31:52.084
