31:55.348 --> 31:56.610
Oh, you see that door?

31:56.740 --> 32:00.048
That is the secret entrance
where Adolph Zukor,

32:00.179 --> 32:02.094
who's the founder of Paramount,

32:02.224 --> 32:03.573
it's where he used to sneak
his little starlets

32:03.704 --> 32:05.488
into his office.

32:05.619 --> 32:07.273
Oh.Ooh.

32:08.970 --> 32:12.452
It's hallowed ground, man.
Hallowed ground.

32:13.018 --> 32:14.802
Ladies, it's time.
Come on, let's go.

32:14.933 --> 32:16.151
Seriously, what's your story?

32:16.282 --> 32:17.631
It's not
terribly interesting.

32:17.761 --> 32:19.763
Worked for Rand Corporation
before "Hogan's."

32:19.894 --> 32:21.765
Architect before that.

32:21.896 --> 32:23.071
Those are both steady gigs.

32:23.202 --> 32:24.855
Why'd you walk away?

32:24.986 --> 32:26.640
Because I could, I guess.

32:29.860 --> 32:32.646
So, Bettye, what's your story?

32:32.776 --> 32:34.169
It's not
terribly interesting.

32:35.605 --> 32:38.521
I'm divorced, opinionated.

32:38.652 --> 32:41.220
The latter most likely
the cause of the former.

32:41.350 --> 32:42.961
Okay,
let's get ready for picture.

32:43.091 --> 32:45.050
Walk it up.I love the movies.

32:46.268 --> 32:48.183
My mom used to take me
every Saturday.

32:48.314 --> 32:49.793
Even when she couldn't make
the rent.

32:49.924 --> 32:52.231
Single mother?Mm-hmm.

32:53.449 --> 32:54.668
Yeah, me too.

32:56.191 --> 32:57.801
Still go every Saturday?

32:57.932 --> 32:59.716
Yes, I do.

32:59.847 --> 33:01.109
I wouldn't miss it
for the world.

33:04.939 --> 33:06.897
How long is your
deal here for, Al?

33:07.028 --> 33:09.074
A year.What, really?

33:09.204 --> 33:11.380
That is not long enough
to start from scratch.

33:11.511 --> 33:13.165
We have to find a script
that's been overlooked.

33:13.295 --> 33:15.080
Places, everybody!
I want to feel some energy!

33:15.210 --> 33:17.299
Well, then
we'd better get started.

33:17.430 --> 33:18.431
Yeah?

33:20.041 --> 33:20.999
Let's watch this take first.

33:21.129 --> 33:22.609
Quiet on set!

33:24.089 --> 33:26.265
"The New York Times'"
Dick Schaap,

33:26.395 --> 33:28.832
"What Philip Roth
did for masturbation,

33:28.963 --> 33:30.312
Puzo does for murder."

33:30.443 --> 33:32.749
"The Post,"
"A searing portrayal

33:32.880 --> 33:34.795
of the mafia underworld."

33:36.927 --> 33:39.800
I'll lay odds that you're gonna
be signing more than 30 books.

33:54.336 --> 33:56.208
Bob, I found something
you're gonna love.

33:56.338 --> 33:58.645
Jesus, Ruddy!
Knock.

33:58.775 --> 34:00.038
It's all right, Sheila.

34:00.168 --> 34:01.517
What was the best scene
in "The Great Escape"?

34:01.648 --> 34:03.041
I don't have time
for party games.

34:03.171 --> 34:04.781
It's McQueen's
motorcycle jump.

34:04.912 --> 34:06.696
Yeah, true.
So what?

34:06.827 --> 34:09.525
I found a great script.
It's about motorcycle racers.

34:10.178 --> 34:12.180
And chicks?Yeah, and chicks.

34:12.311 --> 34:13.660
It's called
"Little Fauss and Big Halsy."

34:13.790 --> 34:15.270
It's perfect for McQueen.Oh, forget McQueen.

34:15.401 --> 34:17.794
For Christ's sake, he's making
his own racing movie,

34:17.925 --> 34:19.622
"Le Mans."

34:19.753 --> 34:21.059
Who else you got in mind?

34:21.189 --> 34:22.712
You need a star, kid.

34:25.106 --> 34:26.412
Robert Redford.

34:26.542 --> 34:29.589
Redford?
Yeah, great idea.

34:29.719 --> 34:31.504
You get me Redford,

34:31.634 --> 34:34.768
you do it for a million five
all-in,

34:34.898 --> 34:36.335
you got yourself a go picture.

34:37.901 --> 34:38.902
Thanks, Bob.

34:39.033 --> 34:41.122
Sure, yeah, yeah.

34:41.253 --> 34:42.602
Evans is messing
with you, Al.

34:42.732 --> 34:44.952
Redford will never do this
for a million five all-in.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.823
How do you know?How is it that you don't?

34:46.954 --> 34:49.391
I don't know. I'm new at this.
Work with me here.

34:49.522 --> 34:50.610
Well, if anyone knows
what Redford's up to,

34:50.740 --> 34:53.091
it'll be Stevie Phillips.Who's he?

34:53.221 --> 34:54.570
She is his agent.

34:54.701 --> 34:56.703
You gotta know
these things, Al.

35:00.315 --> 35:01.925
Stevie Phillips please.

35:03.144 --> 35:04.667
This is Al Ruddy
calling from Paramount

35:04.798 --> 35:07.105
in regards to a project
for Robert Redford.

35:11.587 --> 35:12.632
Yes.

35:14.895 --> 35:16.157
Okay.

35:16.288 --> 35:17.811
Yes, I'll tell him.
Thank you.

35:20.205 --> 35:21.423
Stevie says to call back
when you have more than

35:21.554 --> 35:22.816
"Hogan's Heroes"
under your belt.

35:22.946 --> 35:25.123
Pass.So we go around her.

35:25.253 --> 35:26.602
That's not how things
are done, Al.

35:26.733 --> 35:28.256
I don't give a fuck
how things are done.

35:28.387 --> 35:29.866
Redford's not in town.

35:29.997 --> 35:32.608
He's shooting "Butch Cassidy"
outside San Pedro, Mexico.

35:32.739 --> 35:34.436
Find out
the most expensive hotel there.

35:34.567 --> 35:35.742
That'll be where
Redford's staying.

35:35.872 --> 35:37.700
And then book me a flight.

35:37.831 --> 35:39.137
You are certifiable.

36:04.336 --> 36:06.164
Hey, buddy.
I'm looking for Redford.

36:06.294 --> 36:08.470
And who are you?Producer of his next film.

36:08.601 --> 36:10.211
He said he wanted
to speak to me.

36:10.342 --> 36:12.344
Okay, just--
just wait right there.

36:14.737 --> 36:16.913
Action!
Butch and Sundance, go!

36:24.747 --> 36:25.922
And cavalry, go!

36:33.887 --> 36:35.758
All right.
Cut, cut, cut.

36:36.542 --> 36:38.326
All right.
Great, all right.

36:38.457 --> 36:40.285
Let's get set up
for the next shot.

36:40.415 --> 36:42.243
Let's go, people!
Let's go.

36:42.374 --> 36:44.071
We're burning daylight!

36:44.202 --> 36:45.507
So this is the guy?

36:48.815 --> 36:51.426
Producer of my next film, huh?That's right.

36:51.557 --> 36:53.733
Who the hell are you?Al Ruddy with Paramount.

36:53.863 --> 36:55.778
Huh, Paramount.

36:55.909 --> 36:57.563
Okay, so?

36:57.693 --> 36:58.738
So?

36:58.868 --> 37:00.740
It's a great
Charles Eastman script.

37:00.870 --> 37:02.655
Motorcycles and chicks.
You're gonna love it.

37:02.785 --> 37:04.091
Well, you didn't come
all the way down here

37:04.222 --> 37:06.049
to tell me that.

37:06.180 --> 37:08.704
Yeah, Bob, I did.

37:08.835 --> 37:12.012
Well, you could have called.
Paramount's suing me.

37:12.142 --> 37:14.014
That's why I didn't do
"Rosemary's Baby."

37:15.363 --> 37:17.235
Could've saved you the hassle.

37:18.584 --> 37:20.760
What if I could get you
out of that lawsuit?

37:29.421 --> 37:31.901
You have the authority
to do that?

37:33.338 --> 37:34.730
Yeah, I do...

37:36.515 --> 37:38.952
If you do the movie.

37:43.391 --> 37:45.524
Well, first things first,

37:45.654 --> 37:46.960
how about you and I
go get drunk later?

37:48.440 --> 37:49.397
You tell me who you are
and why I should work with you.

37:51.399 --> 37:52.618
Great.
I'm buying.

37:53.880 --> 37:55.055
No shit.

37:58.885 --> 38:00.103
Yeah.

38:00.234 --> 38:01.540
Ruddy.

38:05.413 --> 38:08.024
"Little Faus and Big Hals."

38:08.155 --> 38:10.505
"Fauss and Halsy."

38:14.509 --> 38:15.902
Ah.

38:16.816 --> 38:19.514
Evans is in this for himself,
not for Gulf and Western.

38:19.645 --> 38:21.299
I give you the reins,

38:21.429 --> 38:24.345
and the problems,
they just magically disappear?

38:24.476 --> 38:26.478
Ah, there's
my favorite Austrian.

38:26.608 --> 38:29.307
I missed this place.
Nice touch, Evans.

38:29.437 --> 38:31.396
Ask and you shall receive.

38:31.526 --> 38:33.659
Been a while since you've
visited the studio, Barry.

38:33.789 --> 38:35.095
Well, that's because
I've been in New York

38:35.225 --> 38:36.575
actually making money
for the company.

38:36.705 --> 38:38.316
Can you say the same?Play nice, children.

38:38.446 --> 38:39.621
Charlie,
you know Ann-Margret, right?

38:39.752 --> 38:41.971
Of course.
One of the greats.

38:42.102 --> 38:43.538
Good to see you, Charlie.

38:43.669 --> 38:45.497
A glass?From you? Sure.

38:45.627 --> 38:46.933
Thank you, honey.

38:47.063 --> 38:49.283
I would love to stay and chat,
but I'm wanted on set.

38:49.414 --> 38:51.416
I'll see you soon?You count on it.

38:51.546 --> 38:52.808
This way,
Miss Margret.

38:54.506 --> 38:56.856
Evans, you are
completely transparent.

38:56.986 --> 38:58.031
Well put.

38:58.161 --> 38:59.815
And I love it!

38:59.946 --> 39:01.948
Cheers.
Help yourself, Barry.

39:02.078 --> 39:04.080
Oh, and, uh, lighten up.

39:04.211 --> 39:05.560
Come on, Cheese.

39:08.781 --> 39:10.391
Ann-Margret
and two flutes of champagne

39:10.522 --> 39:13.176
is not gonna erase
ninth place, Evans.

39:13.307 --> 39:15.091
It's as if every
new Paramount picture

39:15.222 --> 39:16.571
comes with
its own death rattle.

39:16.702 --> 39:19.748
News flash,
you approved them too, Barry.

39:19.879 --> 39:23.186
Jack Warner
on line one for Mr. Bluhdorn.

39:23.317 --> 39:25.058
Jesus. Uh...

39:27.060 --> 39:28.191
Put him through.

39:28.322 --> 39:29.192
Ah, ah, ah.

39:29.323 --> 39:31.020
I don't pick up first.

39:32.195 --> 39:34.372
Jack Warner
doesn't wait on the line.

39:34.937 --> 39:36.156
Neither do I.

39:36.286 --> 39:37.723
You wait for Jack Warner.

39:37.853 --> 39:39.377
Everybody does.
He invented this business.

39:40.029 --> 39:42.902
Uh, Paramount,
holding for Mr. Warner.

39:43.032 --> 39:44.033
Hold please.

39:44.164 --> 39:46.209
Bluhdorn.

39:46.340 --> 39:47.863
Are you there?

39:47.994 --> 39:49.735
Bob Evans, Mr. Warner.
How you doing?

39:49.865 --> 39:51.780
I got Charlie here with me.

39:51.911 --> 39:55.393
Charlie,
you own "The Godfather."

39:55.523 --> 39:57.177
You doing anything with it?

39:57.307 --> 39:58.874
No.Yes.

40:00.354 --> 40:01.573
Well?

40:01.703 --> 40:03.923
We haven't decided.

40:04.053 --> 40:05.490
It's an uncut gem.

40:05.620 --> 40:07.361
Could be a crown jewel.

40:07.492 --> 40:08.710
I've been making
gangster movies

40:08.841 --> 40:10.495
since they were silent.

40:10.625 --> 40:13.236
We know how to make
this work, Charlie.

40:13.367 --> 40:15.108
I'll buy it today
for a million.

40:16.501 --> 40:17.763
Take it.

40:19.068 --> 40:20.330
We'll think about it.

40:20.461 --> 40:21.636
You do that.

40:21.767 --> 40:24.639
I won't wait forever.

40:24.770 --> 40:26.032
What does he know
that I don't?

40:26.162 --> 40:29.949
He knows that there's
movie gold in that book,

40:30.079 --> 40:31.385
which is why we took
a cheap, early option

40:31.516 --> 40:33.909
on the first 60 pages, $15,000,

40:34.040 --> 40:36.564
and that book has been at
number one for the past year.

40:36.695 --> 40:38.653
Barry, why didn't
I know about this?

40:38.784 --> 40:40.307
Yeah.
Why, Barry?

40:40.438 --> 40:42.309
Because our last
gangster movie

40:42.440 --> 40:44.616
was a sugarless turd.

40:44.746 --> 40:46.748
Yeah, because Kirk Douglas

40:46.879 --> 40:49.011
is a goyish Jew
playing an Italian.

40:49.142 --> 40:50.926
We're not gonna make
that mistake again.

40:51.840 --> 40:54.321
Charlie, gangster movies
are dead.

40:54.452 --> 40:56.410
All right? It's a new world.

40:56.541 --> 40:58.368
"James Bond," "Funny Girl,"

40:58.499 --> 40:59.979
that's what people want to see.

41:00.109 --> 41:03.156
Jack Warner, he offers me
a million, we can get three.

41:03.286 --> 41:04.897
Help cover some losses.

41:05.854 --> 41:07.682
Unless I'm missing something.

41:07.813 --> 41:09.510
Evans, what do you see
in this book?

41:10.598 --> 41:12.513
I'll tell you what I see.

41:12.644 --> 41:15.864
I see...money.

41:15.995 --> 41:17.605
This picture can make
Paramount number one, Charlie.

41:17.736 --> 41:19.085
I feel it.
I feel it.

41:19.215 --> 41:20.303
My kishkehs are screaming.

41:20.434 --> 41:21.522
That book's all
anyone's talking about.

41:21.653 --> 41:23.219
Now, you get the right hands
at the wheel

41:23.350 --> 41:24.917
and this could become
a cultural phenomenon,

41:25.047 --> 41:26.527
the likes
we've never seen before,

41:26.658 --> 41:29.487
like "Rosemary's Baby"

41:29.617 --> 41:31.271
but bigger.

41:31.401 --> 41:32.620
A million dollar return

41:32.751 --> 41:35.536
on an investment
of fifteen grand?

41:35.667 --> 41:36.929
We're not gonna get
a better offer.

41:41.237 --> 41:42.935
It's only a million.

41:43.065 --> 41:44.893
Thank you, Charlie.

41:46.460 --> 41:47.548
The bookstore
in Little Italy,

41:47.679 --> 41:48.810
"The Godfather."

41:48.941 --> 41:50.246
58 weeks at number one.

41:50.377 --> 41:51.857
'Cause of the tourists.

41:51.987 --> 41:53.772
Well,
it makes us look stupid.

41:53.902 --> 41:55.295
Like--you know, like a joke.

41:55.425 --> 41:56.818
And that's bad for business.

41:56.949 --> 41:58.646
Sinatra isn't wrong
about this one.

42:10.136 --> 42:12.617
We're here tonight
to acknowledge

42:12.747 --> 42:14.444
Joseph Anthony Colombo,

42:14.575 --> 42:16.664
capo to the Profaci Family.

42:21.887 --> 42:25.673
In recognition for his loyalty
to the commission,

42:25.804 --> 42:29.285
Joe, you have earned a seat
at the table amongst us.

42:30.460 --> 42:33.115
To the Colombo Family.

42:33.246 --> 42:35.988
May you live a long life
with prosperity.

42:36.902 --> 42:37.598
Salute!

42:37.729 --> 42:39.165
Salute!

42:54.659 --> 42:56.574
Some opening weekend.

42:56.704 --> 42:58.576
It's the studio.

42:58.706 --> 42:59.968
They didn't spend enough
on advertising.

43:00.099 --> 43:01.013
That's all.

43:01.143 --> 43:03.232
It's the movie,
not the marketing.

43:03.363 --> 43:04.582
Trust me.

43:06.845 --> 43:08.760
All right.
What are you in the mood for?

43:08.890 --> 43:10.588
I'll take you
anywhere you want.

43:10.718 --> 43:12.807
Nah, honey, I can't.
I gotta get home.

43:12.938 --> 43:14.374
Got a stack of scripts
I need to go through

43:14.504 --> 43:15.462
if I'm gonna
find my next project.

43:15.593 --> 43:16.637
Right now?Yeah.

43:16.768 --> 43:18.073
I thought we were
going to dinner.

43:19.379 --> 43:20.859
You okay
if we get something to go?

43:21.990 --> 43:23.513
If you tell me
what's really going on

43:23.644 --> 43:25.603
in that head of yours.

43:28.780 --> 43:32.610
I'm just scared to lose this,
producing,

43:32.740 --> 43:36.657
and I've never really
felt that before.

43:40.182 --> 43:42.228
Dan Tana's to-go?

43:42.358 --> 43:46.536
Sure.

43:56.155 --> 43:58.026
His secretary say what Evans
wanted to see me about?

43:58.157 --> 43:59.680
No.
But he likes you, Al.

43:59.811 --> 44:01.639
He's probably just checking in
to find out what's next.

44:01.769 --> 44:03.423
My film tanked.
What if he fires me?

44:03.553 --> 44:04.380
Then I'm fired too.

44:04.511 --> 44:06.382
Shit! Hey!

44:06.513 --> 44:07.993
Do not get fired.

44:09.298 --> 44:10.735
Yeah?

44:11.561 --> 44:12.998
Where's the chocolate, man?

44:13.128 --> 44:14.521
I mean,
I don't see any chocolate.

44:14.652 --> 44:15.653
It's a chocolate factory,
right?

44:15.783 --> 44:17.437
You see where
I'm going with this.

44:17.567 --> 44:18.612
Absolutely,
it's devoid of chocolate.

44:18.743 --> 44:21.093
Ruddy, pack your bags.
You're outta here.

44:21.223 --> 44:22.398
Fuck.

44:22.529 --> 44:24.662
New York.
You got a meeting

44:24.792 --> 44:25.837
with Charlie Bluhdorn
first thing in the morning.

44:25.967 --> 44:27.012
What, you thought
you were fired?

44:27.142 --> 44:28.056
That's sweet.

44:29.231 --> 44:29.275
You're not out
of the woods, but, you know.

44:30.319 --> 44:31.712
Okay, yeah.
What--whatever you need.

44:31.843 --> 44:33.366
But, uh, why am I doing this?

44:34.106 --> 44:36.151
You've read
"The Godfather," right?

44:36.282 --> 44:38.240
"The Godfather"?
Sure, who hasn't?

44:38.371 --> 44:39.024
I mean, you've read it.

44:39.981 --> 44:40.634
It's--it's great.
I love it.

44:41.591 --> 44:41.940
Well, you are officially now

44:42.941 --> 44:43.681
Paramount's
low budget specialist.

44:43.811 --> 44:45.160
We've been all over town.

44:45.291 --> 44:46.684
No one wants to make this movie
for four million dollars,

44:46.814 --> 44:48.816
so I need you to produce it.

44:49.774 --> 44:51.123
Get going.

44:52.733 --> 44:54.256
Nice.

44:54.387 --> 44:56.128
And, Ruddy...

44:56.998 --> 44:59.131
Don't fuck it up.

44:59.261 --> 45:00.828
You get 'em?

45:00.959 --> 45:02.830
I can't believe you told him
you read it.

45:02.961 --> 45:04.397
What else was I gonna say?

45:04.527 --> 45:06.181
You better read fast
on the plane.

45:06.312 --> 45:08.183
Fuck, that's big.

45:18.106 --> 45:19.760
It's about an American family.

45:19.891 --> 45:21.893
Bluhdorn is Austrian.
Make it universal.

45:23.764 --> 45:25.461
"The Godfather"
is a Greek tragedy

45:25.592 --> 45:26.854
about an Italian family.

45:26.985 --> 45:28.334
You say the word "tragedy"
to Charlie, and he says,

45:29.901 --> 45:30.858
"The only tragedy of my life
is that I bought Paramount."

45:30.989 --> 45:33.818
Okay,
it's a story about immigrants.

45:33.948 --> 45:35.733
Everybody in America
comes from immigrants.

45:35.863 --> 45:37.735
It's a universal story.You're overthinking it.

45:37.865 --> 45:40.607
Bluhdorn is famous
for being direct.

45:40.738 --> 45:42.740
He speaks like a telegram.

45:42.870 --> 45:44.742
So just be a telegram.

45:46.439 --> 45:47.832
Thanks.

45:59.147 --> 46:00.801
Al Ruddy for Charlie Bluhdorn.

46:00.932 --> 46:02.368
This way.

46:07.286 --> 46:08.461
Al Ruddy.

46:21.996 --> 46:24.129
Americans.

46:26.914 --> 46:29.177
Crime leads to murder
under the...

46:39.448 --> 46:42.408
Holden, you're fired.
Look at the seventh one.

46:42.538 --> 46:44.149
Location, what is that?

46:46.020 --> 46:47.326
Shut up, I don't want
to know what you think!

46:47.456 --> 46:49.894
So you're the genius
that Evans wants

46:50.024 --> 46:52.548
to produce the film
that we should not be making?

46:52.679 --> 46:54.028
You, stay.

46:57.553 --> 46:58.641
Ah.

47:01.427 --> 47:03.908
So tell me, Al Ruddy,

47:04.038 --> 47:06.171
what are you gonna do
with this fucking book?

47:11.567 --> 47:13.134
What?
Is he deaf?

47:22.187 --> 47:24.580
I'm going to make
an ice-blue, terrifying film

47:24.711 --> 47:26.147
about people you love.

47:32.980 --> 47:34.895
That is brilliant!

47:36.941 --> 47:38.333
You, come.

47:42.076 --> 47:43.469
What just happened?

47:44.949 --> 47:46.298
Congratulations.

47:47.429 --> 47:48.909
You're the producer
of "The Godfather."

47:56.003 --> 47:58.310
Ice-blue, baby.

47:58.919 --> 48:00.703
Well, hello
to the ice-blue,

48:00.834 --> 48:02.705
terrifying man of the hour.

48:04.011 --> 48:05.186
Nobody understands
what that means,

48:05.317 --> 48:07.275
but he loved it. Well done.

48:07.406 --> 48:10.061
Now, I wanna talk to you
about writers.

48:11.105 --> 48:14.282
William Goldman, great.
Waldo Salt, excellent.

48:14.413 --> 48:15.893
Look, Bob,
they're great writers,

48:16.023 --> 48:17.807
but we need
a fresh perspective.

48:17.938 --> 48:19.897
We need someone
who understands Italians.

48:20.027 --> 48:20.985
I wanna talk to Puzo.

48:21.115 --> 48:22.682
Oh, sweet Jesus.

48:22.812 --> 48:24.205
Puzo's never written a film.

48:24.336 --> 48:25.598
It's an unwritten law
in Hollywood

48:25.728 --> 48:27.078
that you never hire the author.

48:27.208 --> 48:29.080
They'll turn in
a 500-page first draft

48:29.210 --> 48:30.429
a year fucking late.

48:30.559 --> 48:32.083
Yeah, but he's the guy
with the original idea.

48:32.213 --> 48:33.780
It's at least worth a meeting.

48:34.563 --> 48:36.043
Look, I'm gonna talk to him
while I'm here in New York,

48:36.174 --> 48:38.263
and if I think he's the guy,
will you back me?

48:38.393 --> 48:40.569
Fuck no,
but it's your call.

48:44.095 --> 48:45.400
Everything all right?

48:46.227 --> 48:47.489
When was the last time
you made love in a pool?

49:03.027 --> 49:07.031
Al, I was born
to write this screenplay.

49:07.988 --> 49:09.468
Well, the studio
doesn't believe

49:09.598 --> 49:12.036
that an author
can adapt his own novel.

49:12.166 --> 49:13.385
Then why are you here?

49:14.821 --> 49:15.996
Because I told him.

49:16.127 --> 49:17.606
I said,
"Who knows it better than you?"

49:18.694 --> 49:21.001
Now, look, the movie's in here,
but you gotta carve it away.

49:21.132 --> 49:22.220
Can you do that?

49:23.612 --> 49:24.962
Thank you.

49:27.399 --> 49:29.140
Mario,
he asked you a question.

49:32.621 --> 49:34.188
All right, look.

49:37.713 --> 49:39.106
Fresh start.

49:39.237 --> 49:41.717
But I have to be the one
to write this.

49:41.848 --> 49:43.328
This is my story.

49:43.458 --> 49:46.200
The Corleones are my family.

49:47.897 --> 49:49.943
Can you deliver
a quick draft?

49:50.074 --> 49:51.075
What's quick?

49:51.205 --> 49:52.598
Three months.

49:55.122 --> 49:56.819
You let me do this,

49:56.950 --> 49:59.083
I'll do it in three days.

49:59.997 --> 50:01.389
Who can argue with that?

50:01.520 --> 50:02.695
Three days.
I'm gonna hold you to that.

50:02.825 --> 50:04.218
Hold on, hold on.

50:04.349 --> 50:05.611
I will let you take my husband,

50:05.741 --> 50:09.006
but you must promise me,
Mario has diabetes.

50:09.136 --> 50:10.572
Oh, Erika, please.No. No.

