of the filmmakers.

1:05:45.942 --> 1:05:47.030
Robert Evans and the family

1:05:47.160 --> 1:05:49.771
of Gulf and Western,
the executives.

1:05:49.902 --> 1:05:52.861
And Joe Colombo
and the family of the mafia.

1:05:52.992 --> 1:05:54.211
Salute!

1:05:55.734 --> 1:05:58.693
And bouncing between those
three families is Al Ruddy.

1:05:58.824 --> 1:06:01.870
The story of Al Ruddy
trying to get this movie made,

1:06:02.001 --> 1:06:03.133
and what he and Coppola,

1:06:03.263 --> 1:06:05.439
and everybody went through
to get it made

1:06:05.787 --> 1:06:06.875
is just astounding.

1:06:07.006 --> 1:06:08.312
One of the joys
of the script is,

1:06:08.442 --> 1:06:10.314
is that there's so much tension.

1:06:10.444 --> 1:06:12.185
We know it was made,
and yet when you're doing it,

1:06:12.316 --> 1:06:15.014
you're like, it seems like it
could fall down at any minute.

1:06:15.145 --> 1:06:15.972
We've been all over town,

1:06:17.277 --> 1:06:17.756
no one wants to make this
movie for $4 million.

1:06:18.626 --> 1:06:19.845
So I need you to produce it.

1:06:19.976 --> 1:06:22.021
Not only was he a producer

1:06:22.152 --> 1:06:24.937
that was having to
battle the studio system,

1:06:25.068 --> 1:06:28.201
but he was also battling
the real life mafia.

1:06:28.332 --> 1:06:30.073
For every character
in the story,

1:06:30.203 --> 1:06:31.422
getting this movie made

1:06:31.552 --> 1:06:33.076
or stopping this movie
from being made,

1:06:33.206 --> 1:06:35.252
was a matter of life and death,
literally.

1:06:37.863 --> 1:06:39.778
What I really enjoy about
this character, and with Al,

1:06:40.083 --> 1:06:41.780
is that he's such a man
of action.

1:06:42.085 --> 1:06:44.087
These were some
really serious situations

1:06:44.217 --> 1:06:45.523
that Al was in. Very dangerous.

1:06:45.653 --> 1:06:47.568
You don't like the rules much,
do you Ruddy?

1:06:47.699 --> 1:06:48.308
I don't know the rules.

1:06:49.788 --> 1:06:51.964
You borderline have to be
kind of insane to do the stuff

1:06:52.095 --> 1:06:54.314
that he did
to get this movie made,

1:06:54.445 --> 1:06:58.014
because he really did feel
with every fiber of his being

1:06:58.449 --> 1:07:00.016
that this script was worth it,

1:07:00.146 --> 1:07:01.321
that these actors were worth it,

1:07:01.452 --> 1:07:03.671
that it was all worth it.

1:07:03.802 --> 1:07:07.023
Nice work kiddo, nice work.

1:07:07.545 --> 1:07:09.764
We like to pay homage to
the movie whenever we can,

1:07:10.113 --> 1:07:12.158
and we do it in certain
episodes.

1:07:12.724 --> 1:07:13.681
Hello, Bob.

1:07:15.335 --> 1:07:16.684
There's a specific scene where
that really came home for me.

1:07:16.815 --> 1:07:18.686
Hey, hey, Francis. How you been?

1:07:18.817 --> 1:07:23.604
He is pitching to Ruddy
and Evans in the bar,

1:07:23.735 --> 1:07:24.344
and he says...

1:07:25.650 --> 1:07:28.131
The Godfather
is a story about men.

1:07:28.261 --> 1:07:32.222
Men, brothers, businessmen,
who come together...

1:07:32.352 --> 1:07:35.138
...And they form a bond
and they find justice

1:07:35.964 --> 1:07:37.227
through loyalty.

1:07:38.750 --> 1:07:40.708
And I thought, "Oh, shit! That's
exactly what we're doing."

1:07:40.969 --> 1:07:42.014
It's a metaphor.

1:07:42.145 --> 1:07:43.711
You have
these three brothers

1:07:43.842 --> 1:07:45.104
coming from different places

1:07:45.235 --> 1:07:47.237
coming together to try to get
this made,

1:07:47.367 --> 1:07:49.065
arguing like a family,

1:07:49.195 --> 1:07:50.936
like the three brothers
might be arguing

1:07:51.067 --> 1:07:52.242
in the Corleone family.

1:07:53.678 --> 1:07:54.461
To us, it was important to
follow each of their arcs

1:07:55.506 --> 1:07:56.333
and have each of them
have conflict.

1:07:57.551 --> 1:07:59.814
You read it and you
say, "That's my family."

1:08:00.119 --> 1:08:01.033
They fight.

1:08:01.164 --> 1:08:02.165
They yell at each other.

1:08:02.295 --> 1:08:03.470
They don't like each other
sometimes,

1:08:03.601 --> 1:08:05.081
but at the end, they
come back for each other.

1:08:05.211 --> 1:08:07.213
That is great stuff.
